The paper deals with graph structures and algorithms related to directed graphs, which are common topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The concept of knots and their importance in deadlock detection also suggests a possible category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions clique-width, which is a graph parameter often studied in the context of algorithmic graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the use of feedback vertex sets, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence and machine learning applications (cs.AI).
